            "description": "Returns accuracy metrics for all 8 trained models (RF + GB for each of the 4 components), computed on a held-out 20% test set during training.\n\nMetric guide:\n  R²   — Proportion of variance explained (1.0 = perfect, 0.0 = no better than mean)\n  RMSE — Root Mean Squared Error in km (penalises large errors more)\n  MAE  — Mean Absolute Error in km (average prediction error)\n\nis_best = true marks the winning algorithm for that component."
